  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2455260327" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2455260327" />
    <a title="Joan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3837733-joan"><img alt="Joan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1278652944p2/3837733.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2455260327?book_show_action=true">Jul 13, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Joan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Joan" href="/user/show/3837733-joan">Joan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3837733-joan?shelf=adult-books">adult-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3837733-joan?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3837733-joan?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3837733-joan?shelf=sci-fi">sci-fi</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2455260327" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11987217032221934589">This is the one I dislike the most in this otherwise wonderful series. Anthony mentioned in his author&apos;s note that he had to do a fair amount of research for this title. It shows. Instead of it being incorporated more easily there are large infodumps in this title which are mostly confusing rather than interesting. He also mentioned Asimov in his note. He needed to leave the hard science to Asimov in my opinion. Another problem is that a substantial amount of the book is simply Norton trying to </span>
  <span id="freeText11987217032221934589" style="display:none">This is the one I dislike the most in this otherwise wonderful series. Anthony mentioned in his author's note that he had to do a fair amount of research for this title. It shows. Instead of it being incorporated more easily there are large infodumps in this title which are mostly confusing rather than interesting. He also mentioned Asimov in his note. He needed to leave the hard science to Asimov in my opinion. Another problem is that a substantial amount of the book is simply Norton trying to figure things out in a logical manner. Again, it was not terrifically interesting. I suspect Anthony was trying to show his audience how to reason things out but it was not a well done lesson. Finally, Satan seems more two dimensional in this title than in "On a Pale Horse". Luckily I know I loved the rest of the series so I'm willing to take a chance on it since otherwise I dislike this title enough I doubt I'd read the rest of the series. I was rather hoping I'd like this title better now that I have more time but time didn't seem to help me understand Chronos any! Recommended to those who loved Pale Horse enough to want to read the entire series. I promise you it gets better. Addendum 12/2019: this time around I appreciated the story more. I’m not sure what is really different but I enjoyed the story more and found it more immersive than before. I’m going to advance this up to three stars from two. My complaints about Satan are still valid. I didn’t find the info dump as annoying, perhaps because I understood how it tied into Norton’s dilemmas better. It still is my least favorite of a superb series but I like it better than I did in the past. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11987217032221934589" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

